This paper focuses on analyzing face-to-face interactions and mobility patterns of employees in a research laboratory, which falls under the category of social networks and computational social science. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the layout and physical spaces of the workplace, which could fall under cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Additionally, the paper discusses how cultural differences may influence inter-group interactions, which could fall under cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
